('&#34;Una visiÃ³n de la creaciÃ³n contemporÃ¡nea desde el Mus', 'Manuel Borja-VillelÂ es, desde 2008, director del Museo Reina SofÃ­a de Madrid (MNCARS). Dirige el museo de la FundaciÃ³n Antoni TÃ pies de Barcelona desde su inauguraciÃ³n, en 1990, hasta 1998. Licenciado en Historia del Arte por la Universidad de Valencia, completa su formaciÃ³n como special student en Yale University. En 1989 obtiene el Doctorado en FilosofÃ­a en el Departamento de Historia del Arte en Graduate School of The City University (Nueva York). ', '2015-11-26 19:30:00', 'Performing & Visual Arts', 'FactorÃ­a Cultural / Vivero de Industrias Creativa', 'ES', 'madrid', '14 Paseo de la Chopera, Madrid, ES', 40.4167754, -3.7037902, 'http://www.eventbrite.es/e/entradas-una-vision-de-la-creacion-contemporanea-desde-el-museo-reina-sofia-con-manuel-borja-villel-19165460408?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'images/eventbrite.jpg'),
('&#39;Intelligent Happiness&#39; with Nic Marks', 'Join us for an inspiring evening with Nic Marks as he explores how we can be more &#39;intelligently happy&#39; at work and beyond. \nDoes success lead to happiness? What makes for a happy work life? Can we create more happiness in our daily lives? And how can we contribute to a happier world? Nic will explore these questions and more in a thought-provoking and interactive session. \n \n\n&#34;Nic Marks has an idea worth spreading. We were very happy at TED to give him a platform to share his worldview which he did with eloquence, passion and charm&#34;Â ~ Chris Anderson (TED Curator) \nAbout The Speaker \nNic Marks is a world-renowned expert in happiness and wellbeing. He founded the Centre for Wellbeing at the New Economics Foundation, where his pioneering work included the Five Ways to Wellbeing and Happy Planet Index. He has been a board member of Action for Happiness since before its launch andÂ is now founder director of Happiness Works. \n  \n&#34;I have participated and organized several Conferences on Well-being. Nic is the most inspiring and charismatic speaker on the subject&#34;Â ~ Robert Manchin (Chairman and Managing Director, Gallup) \n \n\nLocation and TimingsÂ  \nThis event will take place at Conway Hall in central London on Tuesday 10 November 2015. Doors will open at 18:30 and the event will start at 19:00 \n \nTickets \nThis event is in support of Action for Happiness. We want to make it accessible to as many people as possible, so rather than charging a fixed fee we&#39;re instead asking you to make a donation. It would be great if you could donate Â£20, but if you can spare more, or feel unable to give that much, then please give what you feel is appropriate. \nAny funds raised (beyond the costs of the event) will contribute directly to Action for Happiness&#39; work relating to growing the movement and supporting local action groups relating to happiness and well-being. Action for Happiness i