('Carols by Candlelight 2015', '&#34;A man is at his finest towards the finish of the year;  He is almost what he should be when the Christmas season is here;  Then he&#39;s thinking more of others than he&#39;s thought the months before,  And the laughter of his children is a joy worth toiling for&#34; \nFrom &#34;At Christmas&#34; by Edgar Guest \nCome and join our celebrity supporters and special guest performers at Carols by Candlelight, in aid of the NSPCC&#39;s ChildLine service. It&#39;s the perfect way to celebrate the beginning of the Christmas season at beautifulÂ Christ Church in Spitalfields. \nGuests will enjoy performances from BBC Young Musician of the Year , Martin James Bartlett, and sing along to traditional Christmas carols to get into the festive spirit. \nThe event will feature readings from celebrities including former Bond girl and Game of Thrones star Dame Diana Rigg and British actress Amanda Donohoe. Previous readers have included Sir Michael Caine, Samantha Bond,Â Sir John Hurt, James Norton, Joely Richardson and Jim Broadbent. \nVIP tickets are also available, priced at Â£85, including a post-concert reception in the historic church&#39;s crypt where guests will be able to mingle with celebrity readers and enjoy Christmas cocktails and canapes, a festive silent auction and special performances from The Victory Sisters. \nCelebrateÂ the very beginning of Advent by buying an official Lindt Advent Calendar, kindly donated by Lindt. Look out for these on the Registration Information page once you&#39;ve selected your tickets and pickÂ them up on the night! \nIn aid of \n \nÂ  \nMedia Partner \n \nEnergy Partner \n \nÂ  \nFAQs \nWhat are the ticket options? \n\nVIP Tickets: Â£85 (child Â£50) - Includes a Tier A concert ticket and entrance to an exclusive sparkling post-concert reception in the crypt with the celebrity readers. VIP Reception includes performances by The Victory Sisters, festive photobooth, hot canapÃ©s, Christmas cocktails, prosecco and a silent auction featuring perfect Christmas presents\nTier B Tickets: Â£35 (child Â£20)\nTier C Tickets: Â£15 (child Â£8)\n\nÂ  \nWhat is the layout of the seating tiers? \nPlease see a diagram below showing the ticket type areas: \n \nÂ  \nWhat are the timings of the event? \nMedia partnerÂ Harper&#39;s BazaarÂ is hosting a pre-concert Reader Event. This will commence at 5.30pm. Doors will open at 6.30pm for the carol concert which will commence at 7.15pm, finishing at 8.30pm. The exclusive post-concert reception will take place in the crypt after the carol concert and will finish by 10pm. \nÂ  \nHow do I book theÂ Harper&#39;s BazaarÂ pre-concert Reader Event? \nTo book the Harper&#39;s Bazaar private event at Carols by Candelight please enter your promotional code above the &#39;Order Now&#39; button at the top of this page. The code can be found on the VIP page of the November 2015 issue (on sale October 1st) or on the onlineÂ Harper&#39;s BazaarÂ VIP event listing page. \nÂ  \nWhere can I contact the organiser with any questions? \nIf you have any queries, please emailÂ mary.dobson@nspcc.org.ukÂ or call 020 3772 9500. \nÂ  \nWhat is the refund policy? \nAll tickets are non-refundable. \nÂ  \nCan children attend the event? \nYes children can attend, with an accompanying adult. Tickets areÂ available at eachÂ price level for children under 16 years old. The concert is more suitable for over-5&#39;s.  \nÂ  \nIs there a dress code? \nThere is no dress code. \nÂ  \nIs there disabled access? \nThere is a ramp and lift suitable for wheelchair users to access the Nave of Christ Church. A disabled toilet is also available.Â  \nÂ  \nCan I make a donation on the night? \nYes, there will be a collection during the evening.Â  ', '2015-12-01 18:30:00', 'Charity & Causes', 'Christ Church Spitalfields', 'GB', 'London', 'null, London, GB', 51.5073509, -0.1277583, 'http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/carols-by-candlelight-2015-tickets-17965410025?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', '