('Certified Scrum Master (CSM)', 'THIS COURSEÂ IS NOT FREE! \nFor moreÂ information about payment, please contact Agilecoach.lt (mokymai@agilecoach.lt or +370 610 75 733) \nÂ  \nDescription: \nIn this 2-day ScrumMaster Certification course we will cover the fundamental principles of Scrum, qualifying the participants as Certified ScrumMasters. Rather than plan, instruct and direct, the leader of a Scrum team (ScrumMaster) facilitates, coaches and leads. \nIn this intensive and highly interactive workshop you will get the opportunity to learn to deal with the obstacles that confront Scrum teams. There will be a variety of exercises and take-aways to use with co-workers. During the course the attendees will learn why such a seemingly simple process as Scrum can have profound effects on an organization. \nTaking a CSM course and the corresponding evaluation designates you as Certified Scrum Master, which indicates that you have been introduced to the basic concepts you need to perform as a Scrum Master or team member on a Scrum team. This course also satisfies two elements of the CSD â€“ track Scrum Introduction and Elective. This course allows delegates to gains an appreciation of the Scrum Framework and how to apply it in their own context. \nÂ  \nWho should attend? \nAnyone interested in starting a Scrum project or wishing to improve their current Scrum implementation. \nThis course has been certified by the Scrum Alliance. Successful completion of this course leads to delegates obtaining the Certified Scrum Master certification as authorised by the Scrum Alliance. In addition, delegates receive 2 years&#39; free membership to the Scrum Alliance. \nÂ  \nMore information: http://agilecoach.lt/mokymai/mokymu-klases/certified-scrum-master/ \nÂ  \nPrice: \nEarly bird price (tillÂ February 1st): 929 Eur (VAT not applicable) \nRegular price: 1049 Eur (VAT not applicable) ', '2016-03-07 09:00:00', 'Business & Professional', 'Europa City Vilnius Hotel', 'LT', 'vilnius', 'J. Jasinskio g. 14, Vilnius, LT', 54.6871555, 25.2796514, 'http://www.eventbrite.com/e/certified-scrum-master-csm-tickets-19478181766?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'images/eventbrite.jpg'),
('Certified Scrum Product Owner (CSPO)', 'THIS COURSEÂ IS NOT FREE! \nFor moreÂ information about payment, please contact Agilecoach.lt (mokymai@agilecoach.lt or +370 610 75 733) \nÂ  \nDescription: \nThis 2-days course highlight how strong Product Ownership is key to a successful agile transformation. \nThe CSPO course gives you just enough information to understand how Scrum works, but focuses mainly on functioning as the product owner or customer, for a Scrum team. You will learn about activities such as managing stakeholders, ROI, backlog grooming, creating effective stories, acceptance criteria for stories, defining done, and so on. \nNot only will the course enable you to understand the product owner role in depth, it will also enable you to lean the practices necessary to succeed as a product owner. \nIn this course we will explain how particular Agile or Scrum role typically manifest themselves in enterprise environments. The course is an interactive workshop filled with lots of exercises whose goal is to demonstrate the difference between traditional and agile approaches to product management and software development. We will also discuss real-world organizational changes such as managing large or multiple teams release planning and tracking progress through the right metrics. Most importantly we will answer your specific questions regarding your individual situation and organization. \nÂ  \nWho should attend? \nThis course is ideal for product managers, analysts, testers, and others who represent and are expected to understand the desires of users and customers on agile projects. You will leave with solid knowledge of how and why Scrum works and of your role on the project. Through practical, hands-on exercises and small-group discussion you will leave prepared to guide a Scrum team to success. \nThis course has been certified by the Scrum Alliance. Successful completion of this course leads to delegates obtaining the Certified Scrum Product Owner certification as authorized by the Scrum Alliance. In addition, delegates receive 2 years free membership to the Scrum Alliance. \nÂ  \nMore information: http://agilecoach.lt/mokymai/mokymu-klases/certified-scrum-product-owner-cspo/ \nÂ  \nPrice: \nEarly bird price (tillÂ February 1st): 929 Eur (VAT not applicable) \nRegular price: 1049 Eur (VAT not applicable) ', '2016-03-10 09:00:00', 'Business & Professional', 'Europa City Vilnius', 'LT', 'vilnius', 'J. Jasinskio str. 14, Vilnius, LT', 54.6871555, 25.2796514, 'http://www.eventbrite.com/e/certified-scrum-product-owner-cspo-tickets-19478288084?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'images/eventbrite.jpg'),
('Certified Scrum Product Owner Course - Jeff Patton', 'Passionate Product Ownership is a Certified* Scrum Product Ownership course that blendsÂ solid product management,Â user experience design, andÂ design thinking into a collaborative team-based approach to Scrum product ownership. \nThatâ€™s a mouthful of jargon, but whatâ€™s important to know is that thisÂ isnâ€™tÂ just a course about filling the product ownership role in Scrum. Itâ€™s a course that teaches the practices you and your team need to create successful products. \nAn Approach to Successful Product Ownership \nProduct ownership is one of the most critical and most difficult roles in an agile process. \nToo often organizations adopting agile approaches and Scrum are lead to believe a single person in a productÂ owner role is responsible for making all the decisions about the product- down to the last detail. The result is stressed, overworked product owner thatâ€™s become a bottleneck for everyone else in the organization. \nOthersÂ with critical input and valuable skills are often shut out of the process. In the end the product being built gets worse, and people in the company are less happy than ever before.Â But thatâ€™s not the way agile development is supposed to work. \nThis class is about an approach to agile product ownership that does. \nIn this course weâ€™ll teach aÂ team-based approachÂ to product ownership where a product owner leads a small discovery team that includes the roles and skills necessary to create a great product. \nWho should attend this course?\n\nProduct managers, business stakeholders, and product marketing professionals: to understand the practices that lead to valuable products\nUser experience practitioners, and business analysts: to understand the practices that lead to usable and desirable products\nSenior engineers: to understand the practices that lead to feasible products\nProject managers, Scrum Masters, and agile coaches: to understand how to guide successful product discovery and delivery\n\nWhat will you learn in this course?\nThe simple Scrum Framework is an effective product delivery approach, but the hardest part of software development is figuring out exactly what to deliver. \nIn this course youâ€™ll learn: \n\ntheÂ goalsÂ andÂ activities of product discovery.\nto use aÂ dual-track approach to developmentÂ where a discovery track is used to guide rapid learning, and a delivery track is used to guide rapid delivery of validated product solutions.\nhow to useÂ effective product design conceptsÂ andÂ practicesÂ to engage in effective collaborative product discovery work\npractices that blendÂ the best of agile, lean, and user experience thinking. These practices allow small teams to engage in faster more collaborative product design and validation.\nLean StartupÂ andÂ Validated Learning\nDesign Thinking\nWorkshop facilitation andÂ card modeling\nLightweight persona sketching\nUser story mapping\nCollaborative design sketching\nPaper prototyping and testing\nTechniques for finding aÂ minimal viable product\nMVPÂ in a large product release\n\nExpect to get your hands dirty \nYou wonâ€™t spend time dozing to PowerPoint slides.Â Youâ€™ll be up and moving and getting hands-on experience workingÂ in a small collaborative group. \n*This course contains all the necessary instruction to qualify participants forÂ Scrum Product Owner Certification. The certification is given and the status maintained byÂ the Scrum Alliance. To receive the certification, the student need only attend the course. \nTrainer\n \nJeff Patton \nHe helps companies design and create better products.  \nAuthor of User Story Mapping. \nCombo Better Software\nCombine your attendance at Better Software 2015Â with Jeff Patton&#39;s Course andÂ save 20%Â on the Course ticket prices! ', '2015-11-19 09:00:00', 'Science & Technology', 'Grand Hotel Mediterraneo', 'IT', 'firenze', 'Lungarno del Tempio, 44, Firenze, IT', 43.7695604, 11.2558136, 'http://www.eventbrite.it/e/certified-scrum-product-owner-course-jeff-patton-tickets-16353573980?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/http%3A%2F%2Fcdn.evbuc.com%2Fimages%2F12783750%2F2482573212%2F1%2Foriginal.png?h=200&w=450&s=8f78ebb5f149862fc2ef06d1e6204998'),
