('Eurovision? The Initial Period of Europeâ€™s Monetary Union', 'Eurovision? \nThe Initial Period of Europeâ€™s Monetary Union \nWe want to take the 25thÂ anniversary ofÂ eabhÂ as an occasion to look at the initial period of Europeâ€™s Monetary Union (EMU). We would like to have â€˜a Conversationâ€™ with those financiers, politicians, lawyers and academics that were involved in relevant decisions concerning the financial sector 25 years ago â€“ and those in charge today. \nThe European Monetary Union and the introduction of the Euro in 1999 were unexpected achievements without precedent. And expectations were high. The Community anticipated output and productivity growth, the realisation of the free movement of goods, persons, services and capital, the elimination of customs and duties, and in the social sphere, the creation of a European Social Fund. What happened to the hopes and objectives of the Treaty of Maastricht? Have some of them come true? \nDecision-makers today face the challenges of a fractured union; however, not all problems policy makers face today are new. Which crucial turning points or decisions in the history of the Union should and could be revised in order to avoid the mistakes of the past? \nThe full programme is available here:Â  ', '2016-01-29 08:45:00', 'Business & Professional', 'Historical Archives of the European Union', 'IT', 'firenze', 'Villa Salviati  , Firenze, IT', 43.7695604, 11.2558136, 'http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/eurovision-the-initial-period-of-europes-monetary-union-tickets-19292066089?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F16419175%252F78039528343%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D30%252C0%252C966%252C483%26s%3Dbb2a4937cc53a726d9acb88cf3bd016e?h=200&w=450&s=391e70e3b1372e829100d8668a935fcc'),
