('Hoppin&#39; Frog Beer Night! 10+ Rare Beers; Barrel-Aged Sto', 'This Tuesday 10/10 Clinton Hall is hosting a Hoppin&#39; Frog tap takeover! With 10+ Hoppin&#39; Frog beers on tap, Clinton Hall is the ONLY bar in all of NYC to get all the special releases. There are a ton of different beers to try, so bring your friends and RSVP!Â  \n\nTry the fantastic Barrel-Aged Boris (9.4%). Made from B.O.R.I.S Imperial stout that was rated one of the worlds best 50 beers this version has been left in a barrel where it picked up flavors like vanilla, dark fruit, oak and spice!Â \nMissing those pumpkin beers already? Hoppin&#39; Frog has got your back! Try theÂ Barrel-Aged Frog Hollow Double Pumpkin Ale the smooth and spicy pumpkin beer has been aged and mellowed in whiskey barrels!Â \n\nNot into Barrel-Aged beers? No worries, there are a bunch of other great beers from Hoppin&#39; Frog that you can check out below. So hop on down to Clinton Hall this Tuesday and have yourself some great beer!Â  \nThis event is free to attend, pay as you drink. \nThey&#39;ll be serving all sorts of tasty brews! \n \nHoppin&#39; Frog Barrel-Aged B.O.R.I.S. Imperial Stout \nImperial Stout - 9.4% 60 IBUs\nMade from our B.O.R.I.S. Imperial Stout, that was rated one of the World?s 50 Best Beers, and won the Gold Medal at the GABF in 2008. BARREL-AGED B.O.R.I.S. has picked up rich characters of vanilla, dark fruit, oak, and spice. It?s unbelievably complex and savory. \nDoris the Destroyer \nOatmeal Stout - 10.5%\nBeware! Beware! The Double Oatmeal Russian Imperial Stout will destroy your taste buds like no other. More hops and more malt than BORIS create a super deep roasted and full bodied flavor, making this the great, great grand daddy of all stout styles. \nHoppin&#39; Frog Hoppin&#39; To Heaven IPA \nAmerican IPA - 6.8% 68 IBUs\nRaise your glass to the heavens in a toast to HOPS ? the spice of beer! This classic American I.P.A. features the finest American hops to add a spicy, assertive, and citrusy character to its full-bodied, rich malt taste \nHoppin&#39; Frog Mean Manalishi Double IPA \nImperial IPA - 8.2% 168 IBUs\nExplore the extremes of hops, and experience all of their bitterness, flavor and aroma with this Double I.P.A. An extreme, super-assertive and satisfying amount of American hop character is balanced with a toasty, caramelized, intense malt presence. \nHoppin&#39; Frog Silk Porter \nPorter - 6.2% 26 IBUs\nDark, robust and silky-smooth, with many flavors of roasted, toasted and caramel malts. Porter is an old-world beer style, so popular that it helped start the industrial revolution. Taste the history. \nGangster Frog \nIndia Pale Ale (IPA) - 7.5%\nIt is a clean and crisp American IPA, loaded with the absolute finest American hops. A lot of research has gone into Gangster Frog IPA, to feature our new, highly-acclaimed and sought-after CITRA hops that we just received for the very first time. And it also has our favorite highest grade Amarillo and Centennial hops as well, to strike the perfect balance. \nHoppin&#39; Frog Outta Kilter Wee-Heavy Scotch Red Ale \nScottish and Irish Ale - 8.2% 23 IBUs\nRich, malty flavors of caramelized and toasted grains dominate this strong Scotch ale. A hint of rye adds a crisp, Scotch-like, old-world beer character, reminiscent of a simpler life from centuries ago. ?It is a wee bit heavy.? \nBarrel Aged Frog&#39;s Hollow Double Pumpkin Ale \nSpice/Herb/Vegetable Beer - 8.4%\nThe smooth and spicy character of Frog&#39;s Hollow Double Pumpkin Ale is perfectly complimented by aging in used whiskey barrels. The result is a complex, super tasty combination of of flavors that is both satisfying and memorable. \nHoppin&#39; Frog Cafe Silk Porter \nPorter - 6.2%\nPer the label, &#34;Our chocolatey Silk Porter cold-infused with dark-roasted coffee beans to create the smoothest coffee character possible. Fresh-roasted coffee flavors and aromas add the perfect compliment to this old-world beer style, forming a truly savory and memorable memorable flavor experience!&#34; \nGoose Juice \nAmerican IPA - 7%\nAmerican hops dominate this Rye IPA, creating an assertive citrus and passion fruit character. An old-world flavor from rye malt adds the perfect compliment to Goose Juice&#39;s big, satisfying hop flavor and aroma. Originally home-brewed by our beloved brewer Goose, its wonderful combination of flavors inspired us to brew this specialty IPA. \nCheers, \nJoey ', '2015-11-10 18:00:00', 'Food & Drink', 'Clinton Hall', 'US', 'New york', '90 Washington Street, New York, US', 40.7127837, -74.0059413, 'http://www.eventbrite.com/e/hoppin-frog-beer-night-10-rare-beers-barrel-aged-stout-pumpkin-ale-more-tickets-19441384705?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F16619602%252F27533485637%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D0%252C12%252C422%252C211%26s%3D15c73b181f786a16379a5cda405b09b7?h=200&w=450&s=60e3df4cd20aa98e0aa13191f182f766'),
