('Liberty Forum and Freedom Dinner 2015', 'Liberty Forum:Â Nov. 11-12 - Crowne Plaza Times Square Freedom Dinner:Â Nov. 12 - Capitale, 130 Bowery, New York City \nLiberty Forum and Freedom Dinner highlights include: \n\nLiggio Lecture by Professor Randy Barnett, Director of the Georgetown Center for the Â  Constitution.\nAtlas Leadership Academy&#39;s Think Tank Shark-Tank $25,000 competition, sponsored Â  Â by the Rising Tide Foundation\n$100,000 Templeton Freedom Award announcement\n\nDescription: \nFor more than three decades, Atlas Network has been the leading organization for building an international network of free-market think tanks. Atlas Network strengthens the worldwide freedom movement by cultivating a highly effective and expansive network that inspires and incentivizes all committed individuals and organizations to achieve lasting impact. More than 476 free-market partner organizations in over 95 countries work daily to move public policy discussions toward the principles of a free society. \nThe annual Liberty Forum brings together amazing freedom champions from this network to exchange ideas and share strategies. The gala Freedom Dinner serves as a fitting grand finale to this conference, celebrating heroes of the freedom movement and the principles that friends of Atlas Network are advancing worldwide. \nHotel Reservations: \nTo receive the discounted room rate of $329++ call the Crowne Plaza Times Square at 1-888-233-9527 and mention Atlas Network. \nEvent Program: \nVisit Atlas Network.org/LibertyForum to view the most up to date event program. \nSponsor a freedom champion: \nAtlas Network brings Freedom Champions from all around the world to participate in Liberty Forum and Freedom Dinner. With your support, we can bring an individual from places like Ukraine, China, Russia, and Ghana to build a network and learn skills that will help them promote freedom in their countries.Â  \nSponsor a freedom champion by selecting this option in the ticket box above. \nDonate to Atlas Network: \nThe mission of Atlas is to strengthen the worldwide freedom movement by cultivating a highly effective and expansive network that inspires and incentivizes all committed individuals and organizations to achieve lasting impact.Â  \nClick here to donate to Atlas Network! \nQuestions?Â Contact Chelsea Schick at (202) 449-8434. \n\nÂ  \nLiberty Forum ExcursionÂ  \nAmerican Museum of Natural History \nJoin the Atlas Network for a guided tour of the American Museum of Natural History on Friday, November 13th after Liberty Forum.Â \nÂ \nThe American Museum of Natural History is recognized as one of the leading education and scientific research institutions in the world.Â  Our guided tour offers an opportunity to learn about how various families of animals evolved over time, differentiating and adapting to their changing environments. This museum is one of the best places in the world to appreciate the richness of life on earth!\n \nThe $31 fee includes shuttle transportation to/from the Crowne Plaza Times Square, a guided tour, access to special exhibits and an IMAX movie for those wishing to stay and explore!\n \nThe $56 fee includes shuttle transportation to/from the Crowne Plaza Times Square, a guided tour, access to special exhibits and an IMAX, and lunch at Pizzeria Uno.\nÂ \nBuses will depart from the Crowne Plaza Times Square at 9:30 a.m. andÂ Buses will return to the hotel at 12:30 p.m. (for those without lunch) and 2:30 p.m. (for those with lunch).Â \n\nContact Stephanie Lips atÂ 914-484-1523Â or Stephanie@AtlasNetwork.org regarding any questions. \nÂ  \n\nGlobal Board Leaders Summit \nThe Global Board Leaders Summit is an exclusive offering to board members and trustees of Atlas Network&#39;s partner organizations. \nDue to high demand and capacity limitations, we have closed registration for the Summit. If you are interested in attending or have any questions, please contact Matt.Warner@AtlasNetwork.org. \nAt the Summit, you&#39;ll learn how to make the most out of your position as a board member. \nThe event will begin on the evening of Wednesday, November 11 with a welcome dinner and the summit will take place on Thursday, November 12 from 9:00 a.m. until 12:00 p.m. ', '2015-11-11 09:00:00', 'Other', 'Crowne Plaza Times Square', 'US', 'New york', '1605 Broadway, New York, US', 40.7127837, -74.0059413, 'http://www.eventbrite.com/e/liberty-forum-and-freedom-dinner-2015-registration-16199596429?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'images/eventbrite.jpg'),
