('Light in the Darkness: A Good Christmas', 'Light in the Darkness: A Good Christmas \nRowan Williams \nSt Paulâ€™s Cathedral, Tuesday 8 December, 6.30 â€“ 8.00pm \nAdmission Free \n \nChristmas is one of the defining points of the year for all Christians, and one of the most difficult festivals to keep spiritually. Amongst all the parties and presents, the busyness and expectations, can we find a way to the heart of the feast and experience anew the extraordinary story of the birth of God in human form, coming to earth as a vulnerable baby born to a poor family in a dark time? \nÂ  \nAnd if we can, what on earth does it mean? The early church debated passionately who Jesus really was â€“ God, human, or both â€“ and itâ€™s still the question on which our faith turns: who was born in that stable, and how does it matter to our lives today? \nÂ  \n  \nRowan Williams will explore the meanings of Christmas, the darkness and strangeness of the story at the beginning of our faith as well as its message of eternal joy and hope. He will also offer suggestions about how we might reclaim Christmas for our spiritual lives. \nÂ  \nRowan Williams is the Master of Magdalene College, Cambridge,and was formerly both Archbishop of Canterbury and Professor of Theology at Oxford University.A prolific author, two of his recent books areÂ Being ChristianÂ andÂ Choose Life: Christmas and Easter Sermons. \n  \n ', '2015-12-08 18:30:00', 'Religion & Spirituality', 'St. Paul&#39;s Cathedral', 'GB', 'London', 'null, London, GB', 51.5073509, -0.1277583, 'http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/light-in-the-darkness-a-good-christmas-tickets-17604625910?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F14182353%252F102540470739%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D0%252C306%252C714%252C357%26s%3Dad066f72738753a483897f32e01a7d3b?h=200&w=450&s=468d456c747d84589300caffb6b6f248'),
('London Baptist Association 150th Anniversary Celebration', 'On the evening of 15th November 2015 a service of celebration will be held to mark the 150th anniversary of the formation of the London Baptist Association. The theme is â€œIncredible Passionâ€ which is what Charles Spurgeon, William Brock and William Landels had when they founded the LBA. Their key themes were unity, evangelism and church planting. This service will be the culminating event of various gatherings that have taken place throughout 2015 to mark the anniversary. Whilst the service will obviously look back it will also need to look forward to Baptist presence and witness in London in the years to come. \nÂ  \nOne of the significant developments in London over the past 150 years is the growth of London as a global, multi-cultural city. With this in mind, we are delighted that our guest preacher will be the Revd Dr Neville Callam, who is the General Secretary of the Baptist World Alliance. ', '2015-11-15 18:00:00', 'Religion & Spirituality', 'Central Hall Westminster', 'GB', 'London', 'Storey&#39;s Gate, London, GB', 51.5073509, -0.1277583, 'http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/london-baptist-association-150th-anniversary-celebration-tickets-18714015123?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F15600240%252F153274345181%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D6%252C9%252C256%252C128%26s%3Ddf85a39cf51d53be4d8374d32fae9ba3?h=200&w=450&s=a49262111fa0a0e1d54abcc7b2a6bd7c'),
('London Chess Classic: Grand Chess Tour 2015', 'The 7th London Chess Classic, England&#39;s premier tournament, will take place at its traditional venue of Kensington Olympia from Friday December 4th to Sunday December 13th. This year the main event will be a 9-round 10-player super tournament that climaxes the 2015 Grand Chess Tour. \nThe 2015 Grand Chess Tour was founded as a partnership between the Chess Club and Scholastic Center of Saint Louis which stages the Sinquefield Cup, Tower AS who organise Norway Chess 2015 and Chess Promotions Ltd, the rights owners of the London Chess Classic. \nNine players compete in all three Grand Chess Tour events: Magnus Carlsen, Fabiano Caruana, Hikaru Nakamura, Veselin Topalov, Alexander Grischuk, Vishy Anand, Anish Giri, Maxime Vachier-Lagrave and Levon Aronian. The London Chess Classic organisers have nominated Michael Adams as the tenth player. This will mean that the LCC will be the strongest event ever held in the UK. \nEach tournament in the Grand Chess Tour has a prize fund of $300,000 and there is a bonus pool of $150,000 for the top three finishers in the Grand Tour based on their overall performance to make a total prize fund of over 1 million dollars. \nThe rules and regulations of the Grand Chess Tour are here and current standings after Norway Chess are here. The schedule of the main event is here. \nThere will be a chess festival alongside the Classic and details will be announced shortly. \nWe look forward to seeing you! \n\nFor enquiries please contact:Â info@londonchessclassic.com\nPress enquiries please contact: press@londonchessclassic.com\n', '2015-12-04 16:00:00', 'Hobbies & Special Interest', 'Olympia Conference Centre', 'GB', 'London', 'Hammersmith Road, LONDON, GB', 51.5073509, -0.1277583, 'http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/london-chess-classic-grand-chess-tour-2015-tickets-13287889435?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/http%3A%2F%2Fcdn.evbuc.com%2Fimages%2F15292196%2F120269692599%2F1%2Foriginal.png?h=200&w=450&s=f454a0073acdd0a2df4b246b6f2708cb'),
('London Entrepreneurs&#39; Challenge 2015', 'Â  \nE-CHALLENGE WORKSHOPS \nÂ  \nThe London Entrepreneursâ€™ Challenge (E-Challenge) is a workshop programme and business plan competition open to all members of UCL, SOAS, Royal Veterinary College, Birkbeck, and the London Busines School that aims to show participants the process of starting a business by helping them do it for themselves. \nThe competition and events programme was launched for the first time in October 2002 and is now entering its thirteenth year. The programme for this academic year will begin in October 2015 and will run until December 2015. Further details can be found at:Â http://www.ucl.ac.uk/advances/e-challenge. \nThe first stage of the competition will involve producing an executive summary. These will be judged and prizes awarded at a small event in the middle of term. The second stage will aim for a more detailed business plan to be produced for a grand final in December 2015. Throughout the programme there wil be substantial cash prizes totalling Â£15,000! \nJudges will be drawn from across academic disciplines and commercial backgrounds. Teams will be judged on their concept, presentation, analysis and planning. \nThe competition element of the Entrepreneurs&#39; Challenge will be supported by document materials, a series of workshops and mentors that will be available to everyone that takes part. Many of the presenters and mentors will be from external organisations and companies and all are business professionals that have proven their value in the commercial world. \nÂ Workshops for the teams will be held during term time from October to December. \nÂ Topics to be covered, include: \nÂ  \n\nAssessing an idea\nIntellectual property and exploitation\nTeam roles and project management\nFinance and business models\nEntrepreneurâ€™s Boot Camp\n\nÂ  \nFor more information on the E-Challenge please visit the website below. \nhttp://londonentrepreneurschallenge.com/index.html \nÂ  \n\n\n\n\n\nD