('NODENIGHT', 'MercoledÃ¬ 18 novembre dalle 19.00Â MeanMilanÂ ha il piacere di ospitare presso la software factoryÂ Venini42Â due tra gli sviluppatori nodeJS piÃ¹ esperti e conosciuti del panorama tecnico italiano,Â Matteo CollinaÂ eÂ Marco Piraccini. I talk che verranno proposti sono: -Â &#34;We are not Object-Oriented anymore&#34;Â All of you have been taught that GOOD code is Object Oriented. Why do you find so difficult to write distributed code? Why should be that hard to move a piece of code from the current machines to another? With this talk will explore what Object Oriented code is good and not good for, and why the node callback style is awesome. (Matteo Collina) - &#34;How to implement a controller for a home automation system with nodeJS and raspberry PI&#34;Â I took advantage of the renovation of my flat to design a home automation system. To save money, but mainly because I must have the complete control of my system, I have implemented the controller of the home automation system using NodeJS, running on a RaspberryPI (with a full web interface) . In the talk I describe the problems I met (e.g. interaction with the KNX BUS, simulation of physical devices) and the solutions implemented. (Marco Piraccini)  \nFormulaÂ BYOB: come ogni volta non dimenticate birre, bibite, patatine, noccioline, torte salate, dolci, ecc. Vi aspettiamo numerosi. ', '2015-11-18 19:00:00', 'Science & Technology', 'Via Giulio e Corrado Venini, 42', 'IT', 'Milano', '42 Via Giulio e Corrado Venini, Milano, IT', 45.4654219, 9.1859243, 'http://www.eventbrite.it/e/biglietti-nodenight-19329353617?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F16468012%252F127001825951%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D0%252C33%252C1000%252C500%26s%3D91e27c7b2db519f97dbb040834dc6a5e?h=200&w=450&s=41388ceb72fed0fdad4e3c3919c3e3bf'),
('NoEstimates Workshop - Vasco Duarte', 'Stop wasting time and money. \n#NoEstimatesÂ is an approach to software development thatÂ arose from the observation that large amounts of time were spent over the years inÂ estimating and improving those estimates, but we see no value from that investment. \nIndeed, according to scholars Conte, Dunmore and Shens* a good estimate is one that isÂ within 25% of the actual cost, 75% of the time. \nThis is the same as saying: give us your money, we promise not lose more than 25% of itÂ (with a 25% probability that we will lose a lot more). We donâ€™t find that acceptable orÂ productive for our industry. \nThere must beÂ better ways to manage software and productÂ development. \nWhat will you learn in this course?\nIn this workshop we willÂ review and analyze why we do estimatesÂ and howÂ we can improveÂ software and product developmentÂ while reducing the time and money invested inÂ estimating. \nWORKSHOP LEARNING GOALS\nâ€¢Â Decision making frameworksÂ for projects that do not require estimates \nâ€¢Â Investment modelsÂ for software projects that do not require estimates \nâ€¢Â Project managementÂ (risk management, scope management, progress reporting,Â etc.) approaches that do not require estimates \nâ€¢ TheÂ tools and argumentsÂ you need to prove the value of #NoEstimates to your boss \nâ€¢Â How to get startedÂ applying #NoEstimates right away \nâ€¢Â Where is #NoEstimates goingÂ and what are the likely changes to software \ndevelopment that will come next \nTrainer\n \nVasco Duarte \nLean Startup, Agile, Scrum, Business, Management. Speaker andÂ author atÂ NoEstimatesBook.com.Â  \nAny questions?Â \nDo you have other questions you would like to see tackled about #NoEstimates? Send usÂ your questions ahead of the workshop and we will tackle as many of those questions as weÂ can before and during the workshop. \nÂ  \n*Paper referred to by Steve McConnell in his book: Software Estimation, Demystifying the Black Art. \nCombo Better Software\nCombine your attendance at Better Software 2015Â with Jeff Patton&#39;s Course andÂ save 20%Â on the Course ticket prices! ', '2015-11-18 09:00:00', 'Science & Technology', 'Grand Hotel Mediterraneo', 'IT', 'firenze', 'Lungarno del Tempio, 44, Firenze, IT', 43.7695604, 11.2558136, 'http://www.eventbrite.it/e/noestimates-workshop-vasco-duarte-tickets-16580909948?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/http%3A%2F%2Fcdn.evbuc.com%2Fimages%2F12947373%2F2482573212%2F1%2Foriginal.png?h=200&w=450&s=90739379d3ca446b8d6396cb9133afc9'),
