('NYC Wine Week presented by CBS New York', '\nABOUT \nFind the perfect pairing in NYC for just $30. From the casual wine enjoyer to the aspiring sommelier, those who purchase a wristband enjoy 5 days of $4 featured wines and appetizers at participating locations across the city. Donâ€™t miss out on NYC Wine Week, presented by CBS New York.Â  \nÂ  \nPicking up a wristband \nWhere and when can I pick up my wristband? \nYou can pick up your wristband from 5pm-8pm Monday, Nov. 9th through Wednesday, Nov. 11th at the following 2 locations: \n- Ayza, West Village:Â 1 7th Ave S, New York, NY 10014 \n- Flute Midtown: 205 West 54th St., New York, NY 10019 \nÂ  \nWhat bars and restaurants are participating in Wine Week 2015? \nAdding Locations Daily!!Â  \n \nÂ Click here to view a map of all participating locations. \nÂ Printable Wine Week Map here \nÂ  \n\nFAQ \nPurchasing a Wristband \nHow can a friend or I purchase a wristband? \nYou can purchase your ticket online here. Your ticket entitles you to a wristband - you can pick up your wristband(s) at any of the featured bar locations listed below during the week of NYC Wine Week (November 9th â€“ 13th). \nAlternatively, wristbands can be purchased online with direct shipment (at additional cost) of the wristband to your delivery address.Â  \nWhy do I need a wristband? \nThe wristband entitles you to discounted drink or food item(s) at participating locations from November 9th â€“ November 13th. This offer is for select $4 wine and/or food item(s) from Monday to Friday, at any time the participating bars are open. You must wear your wristband in order to qualify for the discount. No exceptions will be made; you must be wearing your wristband as originally placed on your wrist. \nAs we approach the event date, we will post a map to this site for a listing of all participating bars and restaurants along with their offers for the week. Some bars may offer wine-only, other bars may offer food-only, while some others may offer wine and food items. \nIf I donâ€™t get my wristband shipped in advance, what do I need to bring with me when picking up my wristband? \nBring your ticket. This will have the necessary bar code that will be scanned in order to provide you with your wristband when picking it up at any of the hub locations. As an alternative to a printed ticket, download the Eventbrite app in which you can store and present your ticket. You will also be required to present your ID when picking up your wristband at featured bar locations. \nTicket Purchase Rules \nWhat happens if my wristband is lost or damaged? \nWristbands cannot be replaced whether lost, stolen, damaged or destroyed â€“ even with proof of purchase.Â  Wristbands are non-transferable. \nWhat is the minimum age requirement? \nYou must be 21+ to participate in NYC Wine Week. You will be required to present your ID when picking up your wristband at featured bar locations. \nWhat is the ticket purchase policy? \nAll sales are final. No refunds will be issued. If you have a question about or concern with your purchase, please contact us at: eventbritecbs@cbs.com \nWhen can I use my wristband? \nYour wristband will be valid from Monday, November 9th- Friday, November 13th at participating locations. \nCan I buy discounted drinks for my friends? \nUnfortunately, you may not purchase discounted drinks or food for anyone else â€“ no buying rounds or doubling up. Your wristband entitles you personally to the benefits of NYC Wine Week. \nAre there any limitations on the number of drinks or food that can be consumed? \nThere are no limits on the number of discounted drinks or food that you are allowed to consume; however, participating bars and restaurants reserve the right not to serve individuals who they believe to be intoxicated. You should be mindful of how much you consume and ensure you are behaving properly. \nIs there anything else I should know? \nIf youâ€™re thinking about driving, donâ€™t do it.Â  We want everyone to enjoy himself or herself throughout NYC Wine Week, but we want you to get home to tell people about your great time.Â  You should not drink alcohol and then drive and you should not offer alcohol to anyone who will be driving.Â  Have fun and stay safe! \nI have a question that has not been addressed in the FAQs, how can I get the answer? \nYou can reach out with any questions at: eventbritecbs@cbs.com ', '2015-11-09 12:00:00', 'Food & Drink', 'New York', 'US', 'New york', 'null, New York, US', 40.7127837, -74.0059413, 'http://www.eventbrite.com/e/nyc-wine-week-presented-by-cbs-new-york-tickets-18633083053?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F15608344%252F102490648407%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D8%252C6%252C278%252C139%26s%3Dbf2b5749cd703e91309b33d2c37cff06?h=200&w=450&s=9649f94ed931a39dc05a0883e7710169'),
