('Open Day at City of Westminster College / Saturday 7th & Tue', 'Open Day at City of Westminster CollegeÂ  \nSaturday 7th & Tuesday 10th November 2015Â  \nThank you for your interest in attendingÂ our Open Days.Â  \nOur Open Days are designed to enable you to experience first-hand what it is like to study with us. During the event you can attend subject area talks, take a tour of our campus and meet with our friendly teams of staff and students.  We are situated in the heart of central London; just 5 minutes away from Edgware Road Underground Station and 10 mins from Oxford Street. You can also reach us on London Buses, numbersÂ 6, 16, 18, 98, 332, 414 and by rail at bothÂ Paddington and Marylebone Rail Stations, which are only a short walk away.Â  \n Outline of the Day (Saturday 7th November 2015) \nDoors will open andÂ registrationÂ will beginÂ at 9.45am. If you are early and arrive before this time, you can grab a coffee in our onsite Costa.Â  \nOnce you have registered at reception you will be ushered to a subject talk starting at 10.00am for half an hour. Â After this you can visit members of staff around our building or talk to our admissions team or tour the facilities on offer at this campus. Â Talks will take place every hour, the last session will begin at 1pm.Â The event ends at 2pm, last admittance will be at 1.30pm to allow attendees enough time to see members of staff. \nÂ  \nOutline of the Day (Tuesday 10th November 2015) \nDoors will open andÂ registrationÂ will beginÂ at 3.45pm. If you are early and arrive before this time, you can grab a coffee in our onsite Costa.Â Â  \nOnce you have registered at reception you will be ushered to a subject talk starting at 4.00pm for half an hour. After this you can visit members of staff around our building or talk to our admissions team or tour the facilities on offer at this campus. Talks will take place every 30mins, the last session will begin at 7pm*.Â The event ends at 8pm, last admittance will be at 7.30pm to allow attendees enough time to see members of staff. \nFor all events \nProspective students may attend the event with family or a friend- however due to limited space on the subject talks, guests may be invited to tour the facilities, or use our refreshment services.Â  We therefore advise guests to bring a book, magazine or electronic entertainment to make best use of their time between sessions. \nWe hope that you will enjoy your visit.Â  \nâ€¨Once registeredÂ on this web linkÂ please keep checking our City of Westminster College website Open Events page for updates:Â www.cwc.ac.uk Â  We look forward to welcoming you to our College in the near future! \nPlease email any queries to: opendays@cwc.ac.uk \n* Please note under 16s are invited up to our 6.00pm sessions. Prospective students signing up to sessions after 6.00 pm who are under 16 must be accompanied by a responsible adult and ideally parent/carer or guardianÂ to attend events at City of Westminster College.Â Â  \n  \nFAQs Â  How do I register for an Open Day? \nFor all of our courses, please select the time that is right for you from the ticket options. To attend our Open Day you MUST select one of these options.  Do I need to book a place? \nYes, we have a limited number of spaces available for each Open Day and so prospective students must pre-register. You can reserve extra tickets for additional visitors if you would like to bring a relative or friend however you will have to register their details.Â For health and safety reasons, we are not able to accommodate anyone who has not pre-registered. \nWhy can I only book one ticket for each session, I would like to book for my friends as well?Â  \nDue to space limitations and Health & Safety we require each attendee to a session to book a place. If you want to bring friends or family into a session, they will need to book an individual place for themselves. You can also book a place for them with their email address.Â  \nDo I need to book a place for my parent(s) or guardian(s)?Â  \nThere is no need to book an additional for any or guardians who will be accompanying you during the Open Day. However, due to limited space, they may not be able to attend our talks without a ticket. If they do wish to attend a talk, they can guarantee a place by booking a ticket.Â  \nDo I need to bring written confirmation of my booking with me? \nYes, your registration will be recorded on our system; however, having a ticket willÂ quicken the registration process - this can be printed or displayed on your smartphone or handheld device.Â  \nI want to change/cancel the session I registered for?Â  \nOn EventBrite, use the logon details you entered when you registered for our Open Day. From there you will be able to amend your tickets and change your session or cancel your booking. \nWhat time do I need to arrive? \nFor Saturday 7th November, the first talk starts at 10am and the last talk starts at 1pm. There are scheduled talks every half hour between 10am and 1pm for all of our taught courses - please arrive at least 15 minutes before your chosen talk in order to check in.Â  \nFor Tuesday 10th November, the firstÂ talk starts at 4pm and finish by 7.30pm. There are scheduled talks every half hour between 4pm and 7pm for all of our taught courses - please arrive at least 15 minutes before your chosen talk in order to check in.Â   Where is City of Westminster College? \nPaddington Green Campus (PGC), Paddington Green, London W2 1NB \nClick here to find us on Google Maps.  How do I get to City of Westminster College? \nWe are easily reached by the London Underground, bus, and rail. The nearest tube and bus stop is Edgware Road and we are a five minute walk away from the station.Â Click here for transport information and maps.  Do you have car parking facilities? \nWe are unable to offer onsite parking facilities.  Do you have bicycle storage facilities? \nYes, we have a small number of covered bicycle racks located to the side of our building. Please note that bicycles are left at the individual&#39;s own risk.  Is there anywhere to get something to eat or drink? \nWe have our own Costa cafÃ© on the ground floor of the campus which offers a small selection of snacks and drinks. \nIn addition there are a wide range of cafes and restaurants on the nearby Edgware Road.  Who can attend? \nProspective students can attend together with their parents or a friend or partner. However, guests may not be able to attend the specific talks due to space. We do have a cafe for guests on our ground floor, and many break out areas throughout the campus, and they can also purchase refreshments in the cafÃ© area on the ground floor. \nWhat can I expect from an Open Day? \nAt our Open Days, you will typically listen to subject talks by our academic staff, go on a tour of our building and facilities with some of our students, receive advice on student finance and accommodation, and have guidance on the application process. For Undergraduate courses, you will in addition have the opportunity to discuss your individual situation and career prospects with a team member of the course that you are interested in.  We hope this answers any questions you may have. You can contact us by email if you have an additional query at opendays@cwc.ac.uk  Can I visit City of Westminster College at any other time?Â  \nProspective students can visit our Information Centre during normal College opening hours.Â  ', '2015-11-07 10:00:00', 'Family & Education', 'City of Westminster College (PGC)', 'GB', 'London', 'Paddington Green, London, GB', 51.5073509, -0.1277583, 'http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/open-day-at-city-of-westminster-college-saturday-7th-tuesday-10th-november-2015-tickets-19149507693?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'images/eventbrite.jpg'),
