('Royal Central School of Speech and Drama Graduation Ceremony', 'The Royal Central School of Speech & Drama 2015 Graduation Ceremony will take place at 2.00pm at theÂ Royal Festival Hall, Southbank Centre, Belvedere Road,Â London, SE1 8XX. \nÂ  \n  \nALL GRADUANDS MUST CONFIRM THEIR ATTENDANCE BY ORDERING A GRADUAND TICKET.Â  \n  \nGraduands are seated alphabetically by award, then course name and then their surname at the front of the auditorium. This is the order that graduands process in. \nWe will allocate guest seats in order of receipt of ticket orders and successful payment â€“ please therefore be advised that early bookings will be allocated seats closer to the stage. Further information about the order of ceremony and other events taking place on the day will be sent out closer to the ceremony date.Â The Royal Festival Hall is accessible for people with limited mobility and wheelchair users â€“ further information is available on their website.Â We recommend that children under 7 years of age are not brought to the Ceremony to avoid interruption.Â  \nPlease indicate in the Special Requirements section of the booking process if you or any of your guests have mobility difficulties and what special arrangements may be needed. A number of wheelchairs can be accommodated in the auditorium but need to be notified in advance so that spaces can be reserved. If such requirements are not specified, we cannotÂ guaranteeÂ that suitable seating is provided on the day. \nPlease note that award certificates for all graduands are sent out by the University of London directly to you and are not issued by the School or available at the ceremony. Information about this certificate production process is issued with your results letter. \nPlease note that 30thÂ November 2015Â is theÂ absolute closing dateÂ for graduand bookings to be received by the School.Â If a graduand is in debt to the School when ticket sales close, their order will be cancelled and your attendance at the ceremony prohibited. \n  \nArrival \nThe venue will be open to graduands and their guests from 10.00am. The latest time that you should arrive at the venue is 12.00pm, to allow time for robing and photography, but earlier arrival is obviously recommended to avoid a rush, bearing in mind that all graduands will need to be seated in the auditorium by 1.00pm prompt for a briefing. The auditorium opens for guests at 2pm andÂ all should be seated by 2.20pm for the start of the ceremony. \nÂ  \nDress \nYou will beÂ requiredÂ to wear an academic gown, hood and hat for the Ceremony. You must make your own arrangements for gown and hat hire through the academic outfitters Ede & RavenscroftÂ by visiting theirÂ Graduation Services website. You will see that they advise you to place your order at least 21 days before the Ceremony, i.e. before 16th November. Your order will then be available for collection on the day at the Royal Festival Hall. \nPlease ensure that you do make your booking as we will have to turn away anyone arriving at the ceremony without arrangements for a gown and hat. Please also note that when selecting your gown, you need to specify both University of London and Royal Central School of Speech & Drama, as well as your qualification (i.e. BA, MA, PGCE, etc). Further guidance is available on the Ede & Ravenscroft website.Â  \nGown, hood and hat designs \nUniversity of London Bachelor of Arts \nUniversity of London Master of Arts \nUniversity of London Diploma and Certificate \nUniversity of London Doctorate \n  \nPhotographs \nInformation for photography services through Ede & Ravenscroft is also available and you are advised to make your arrangements as early as possible if you wish to pre-order photographs. Please note that you must pay for any photographs that you order. Visit the Graduation Services websiteÂ to make your booking. \nIt will be possible to have your photographs taken from 10.30am on the day and all photographs must be completed before the ceremony starts. \nÂ  \nGraduation Memorabilia \nA special â€˜Class of â€˜15â€™ t-shirt and hoodie are being produced by Campus Clothing, with the names of all 2015 graduates printed on the back.Â Â Information about the styles on offer, other memorabilia and the ordering arrangements are available on their website. These can be ordered in advance and collected on the day, or bought on the day, or they can be posted on to you afterwards.Â Â  \nÂ  \nAlumni Association \nPlease take the time to visit the Alumni Office stand, where you can learn more about how to stay in touch with Central after you graduate, and also collect your free copy of the Alumni Newsletter. For more information about what it means to be a Central graduate please visit the Alumni webpage.Â  \nVideo \nThe Ceremony will be projected on a large screen at the venue.Â  \nRefreshments \nIt will be possible for you and your guests to have lunch in the Royal Festival Hall, or alternatively there are a wide range of local cafes and restaurants nearby on the South Bank. Reservations can be made at some of these and others operate on a â€˜walk inâ€™ basis - further information and contact/booking details are given on the Southbank Centre website. \nPlease note that the Ceremony and any celebrations that follow will formally be over by 5.00pm, but the public areas of the Royal Festival Hall will remain open to guests. \nÂ  \nThe School very much hopes that you will be able to attend the Graduation Ceremony to celebrate your great success with family, friends and staff and we look forward to seeing you in December. \nÂ  \nYours sincerely, \nÂ  \nAcademic Records Office \nTel: 020 7449 1640 \nEmail:Â aro@cssd.ac.uk \nÂ  \nN.B. All orders for gowns and hats, photographs, catering and T-shirts, should be made direct with the companies concerned. The School has no responsibility for these and no orders should be sent to us. \nÂ  \nPLEASE NOTE THAT 30th NOVEMBER 2015 IS THE ABSOLUTE CLOSING DATE FOR GRADUAND BOOKINGS TO BE RECEIVED BY THE SCHOOL AND WE WILL NOT BE ABLE TO ACCEPT ANY AFTER THIS DATE OR ON THE DAY OF THE CEREMONY \nÂ  \nFAQs \n  \nIs my registration/ticket transferrable to another graduand? \nNo. Please do not transfer your tickets to a friend as we need to know which graduands are attending and which aren&#39;t. Please cancel your tickets if you or any of your guests are unable to attend. \nÂ  \nDo I have to bring my printed ticket to the event? \nYes. Bringing your printed tickets will avoid any confusion over bookings but staff at the registration desks will be able to check your booking online if necessary. \nÂ Â  \nWhat is the refund policy? \nRefunds are offered via email request up until 5pm on Friday 4th December 2015. Please contact us at aro@cssd.ac.uk. Funds are refunded through Eventbrite and there is a delay. \nÂ Â  \nThe name on the registration/ticket doesn&#39;t match the guest. Is that okay? \nYes. We have made it possible for friends and relatives to book tickets for graduands but ask that all orders are linked to a graduand by entering their name and course during the ordering process. \nÂ  \nCan I book tickets before I clear outstanding debt with the School? \nÂ Yes. You can make a booking, but this will be cancelled if the debt is not cleared by 31st November 2015. Any guest tickets not linked to a graduand may not be refunded unless explicitely requested by 31st November 2015. \n  \nCan graduands process on stage without wearing a cap and gown? \nNo. It is a formal requirement of graduands to process in full academic dress. Graduands will be prevented from processing if they are in line but are not wearing their academic dress.Â Graduands who wish to attend the ceremony, but not hire from Ede & Ravenscroft, can sit with guests in the auditorium and should indicate this on their booking in the Special Requirements section. ', '2015-12-07 14:00:00', 'Family & Education', 'Royal Festival Hall', 'GB', 'London', 'Belvedere Road, London, GB'