('Source of Well-Being - If you&#39;re a cow you don&#39;t hav', '3P-Akademiet(norway) and One Thought hereby invite you to this two day exploration into the source of well-being.Â   Aaron Turner and Mara gleason fron One Thought are coming to Norway to do a training for practitioners in our field here in NOrway, and we have decided to open up two of the days for people, including a public talk. We are excited to present this opportunity, and canÂ´t wait to see you there. Read below about the event itself, and sign up asap to benefit from the Earlybird :)Â    \nSource of Well-BeingÂ  \nIf youÂ´re a cow you donÂ´t have to go to the store to buy milk \n \nPerhaps the most common thing among human beings is that we all want to feel a sense of well-being.Â  While you may call that happiness, less stress, balance, peace of mind, or just the desire to get through the day feeling normal...we all want to feel whatever we think of as WELL. Throughout the ages, people have pursued psychology, spirituality, religion, philosophy, therapy, practices, tools, techniques, coaching, and more in an attempt to feel a greater sense of well-being in life.Â  While all of those pursuits can sometimes enrich a person&#39;s life, none of them singularly defines the universal source of well-being for humankind.Â  Because they do not define the source, they are further downstream, pointing more toward things people can DO to try to feel wellÂ after the fact.Â  That can ultimately lead people to a lot of &#34;doing&#34; in life, so much so that it can feel exhausting and frustrating.Â  However, understanding the source of our well-being frees us from all the doing.Â  As Aaron likes to say, &#34;When you realize you ARE the cow, you can stop going to the supermarket and buying milk every day.Â  You are the source of milk.Â  You don&#39;t have to go pay for it packaged somewhere else.&#34; \nÂ \nJoin us in this 2-day discussion about the internal principles that explain where our well-being resides, and why we feel it when we feel it and why we feel we lose it at times.Â  Through a combination of teaching and discussions, we will guide you in discovering the source of well-being inside yourself, and the unconditional potential to experience it more consistently in your life.Â  Without any of your external circumstances changing, you will find yourself feeling more clarity, resilience, freedom of mind and wellness just by gaining a deeper understanding of the mind.Â \nÂ \n\n About the speakers\n\n\nÂ Aaron Turner-Â Co-Founder One thoughtÂ \n\n\n\nAaron earned his Ph.D in Anthropology from Londonâ€™s Brunel University and joined Pransky and Associates, a world leader in the pioneering approach to human potential. During his decade-long tenure there, Aaron played a key role in the expansion of the practiceâ€™s work in business. \nHe successfully applied an innovative approach to address challenges met by senior management at large corporations. Aaron developed applications and courses in leadership and cultural change, leveraging team performance, and creating a foundation for his clients to improve customer loyalty and increase earning potential. Â Aaron is a recognized international speaker in the State of Mind field, and educates executives in the private and public sectors. Â In 2010, Aaron co-founded One Thought with Mara Gleason to expand his practice through the development of the One Thought Practitioner Training. Â He is married to Lila, the One Thought Director of Personal Programs. \nMara Gleason-Â Co-Founder One thoughtÂ   \n\n\nMara has an MSW from Columbia University and served as a senior consultantÂ for Pransky and Associates, one of the pioneers in State of Mind training and the development of human potential. Â Mara has dedicated the last ten years to the discovery of how State of Mind processes can reap huge benefits for individuals, organizations and corporations. She and Aaron Turner began One Thought as a testament to their dedication and interest in fundamentally improving the way we perform. Â She is sought after as a speaker on the techniques used to unleash a ripple effect of global positive change. Â  \n\nAny questions?Â  \n\n\nSend an email to the host eirikgolsen@gmail.comÂ  \n\n\n', '2015-11-20 18:00:00', 'Health & Wellness', 'Oslo', 'NO', 'oslo', 'null, Oslo, NO', 59.9138688, 10.7522454, 'http://www.eventbrite.com/e/source-of-well-being-if-youre-a-cow-you-dont-have-to-go-to-the-store-to-buy-milk-tickets-18805893935?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F15735183%252F47455691677%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D12%252C66%252C642%252C321%26s%3Dcc76f9abe75616a18635224c09695b2d?h=200&w=450&s=6d5f0b43f648b263fde087386aff91bd'),
