('Startup Grind Bratislava Hosts Michal Stencl (Sygic)', '\nMichal Stencl, Sygic \n\n\n\nMichal Stencl    Founder & CEO of Sygic    As only an 8 year old, Michal got his first computer and in 13 he started to programm his own operating system. He graduated from University of Economics in Bratislava and few years later he also attended Stanford University Graduate School of Business. Even during his studies he was programming an operating system for mobile phones. After he graduated, he got an offer to work in the USA, but he declined and stayed in Slovakia. In 2004, when he was only 25, he founded his own navigation company â€“ Sygic. Sygic develops, markets and sells the leading gps navigation software Sygic GPS Navigation for smartphones, keeping the top positions on both Android and AppStore market places. Sygic has been recognized as the very first company worldwide that has launched the gps navigation software for Apple AppStore (in 2009) and second in the world, which introduced navigation for Google Android.    Now, Sygic has reached 100 million users milestone (is used in more than 101 countries) and more than 10.000 business customers including governments world-wide. This Slovak GPS is installed in over a 50 million mobile phones, which makes it the worldÂ´s most downloaded offline navigation! Sygic also partners with premium car makers to delivery incar connectivity to its products.    Michal, with his company, recieved many awards, such as Deloitte Fast 50 (2007, 2008, 2009 â€“ Rising star in Central Europe ranked on 6th and also 2nd position; 2010 Central Europe and EMEA 500 with 995% growth in last 5 years), Ernst & Young (Entrepreneur of the Year 2009) and Slovak award called â€žKristalove kridloâ€œ in Economy sector for the year 2012.    His desire is to work on public transport and its solutions, how will people move in the future. \n\n\n\n\n\n\nAgenda\nÂ \n6:00\nNetworking and Food\n\n\n7:00\nFireside Chat\n\n\n8:00\nNetworking\n\n\n\n\nHosted By \nMarek Zamecnik, Director of Startup Grind Bratislava \n\n\n Â  Prior to co-founding RubixLab, Marek was active in a VC firm â€“ Nova Founders Capital in Southeast Asia where he was responsible for venture development. While at Nova Founders he also organized the largest private equity conference in Switzerland. During his academic years he finished 2nd in the world in global startup competition. Marek studied at various universities in four different countries such as the University of Manchester, Copenhagen Business School, Oxford Brookes University, or UniversitÃ© Paris Dauphine.  Email: Marek@startupgrind.com \n\n\n\nHosted By \nKristÃ­na JanÄinovÃ¡, Director of Startup Grind Bratislava \n\n\n KristÃ­na facilitates the newly established chapter of Startup Grind in Bratislava, Slovakia, where she was born. Simultaneously she is responsible for all events at RubixLab (international concepts like this but also local and smaller ones). She recently got her MasterÂ´s degree in Marketing Communication and is always excited to meet new people, explore amazing startup scenes internationally and learn new things as well. She has been active with startups for the past year and a half. KristÃ­na loves music, movies & TV series, bake healthy cakes and helps animals.  Email: Kristina@startupgrind.com \n\n\n\nGlobal Partners \n\nGoogle is committed to empowering entrepreneurs around the world through programs, partnerships, and our products. \n\n\n\nLocal Partners \n\nCentral European based business incubator focused on early stage startups. \n\n\nKPMG is a global network of professional services firms with offices in 155 countries all around the globe and over 155,000 experts in fields of mergers and acquisitions, tax, legal, audit and other advisory support. KPMG in Slovakia has been working with selected founders and their startups for the past several years within The Startup Studio and leads the preparation of the annual Startup Survey which offers a snapshot of the Slovak startup ecosystem. \n\n\n \n\nWhat is Startup Grind? \nStartup Grind is a global startup community educating, inspiring, and connecting entrepreneurs. We host monthly events in more than 150 cities and 65 countries featuring successful local founders, innovators, educators and investors who share personal stories and lessons learned on the road to building great companies. Our monthly fireside chat interviews, startup mixers and annual conferences provide ample opportunities to connect with amazing startups and the people behind them, tap into a strong support network, form meaningful connections and gain inspiration for the startup journey ahead. For more information visit StartupGrind.com or follow us on twitter @StartupGrind. \n\n \n\nDisclaimer: Startup Grind event ticket sales are non-transferable, non-refundable, and final. If an event is cancelled due to weather, speaker availability, or any other unforeseeable event you will be refunded automatically. If a speaker moves the event date you will have 48-hours to request a refund if you are unable to make the new event date. Please direct any additional ticketing issues to customerservice@startupgrind.com. \n', '2015-11-19 18:00:00', '', 'Impact Hub Bratislava', 'SK', 'bratislava', 'Hviezdoslavovo nÃ¡mestie 20, Bratislava, SK', 48.1458923, 17.1071373, 'http://www.eventbrite.com/e/startup-grind-bratislava-hosts-michal-stencl-sygic-tickets-18536203283?aff=ebapi', 'eventbrite', 'https://img.evbuc.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimg.evbuc.com%2Fhttp%253A%252F%252Fcdn.evbuc.com%252Fimages%252F15444642%252F147092265439%252F1%252Foriginal.jpg%3Frect%3D0%252C1%252C746%252C373%26s%3D5c6af9672e8587dee949da35bdd5c96d?h=200&w=450&s=269daa70f168274dab85597b40a819bb'),
